fields.description:
Workflow executions created by CloudFormation currently have one of the tags:

* CreateStackWorkflow
* DeleteStackWorkflow

which do not help identify the workflow execution that relates to a specific CloudFormation stack.

We should tag the workflow executions with correlation information to simplify debugging / management of workflow executions (as workflow executions can be listed by tag)
fields.summary: CloudFormation managed (SWF) workflow executions should be tagged with identifying info

comments.body:
4 SWF tags are added per workflow

StackId:<stackId>
StackName:<stackName>
AccountId:<AccountId>
AccountName:<AccountName>

These values can be checked by running the getWorkflowExecutionHistory command against SWF

[~ethomas],

Looking in the DB, where can I find runIds that are associated with each workflowId?

[~hspencer]
Tags in the workflows are stored in tables associated with SWF, which [~sjones] would have to elaborate on.  What I do in CloudFormation in the eucalyptus_cloudformation db is have the table stack_workflows which has the columns:  stack_id, domain, workflowId, runId, and workflowType.

workflowType can have values:     
    CREATE_STACK_WORKFLOW,
    DELETE_STACK_WORKFLOW,
    MONITOR_CREATE_STACK_WORKFLOW

On a create stack call, two workflows are kicked off.  One to create the stack itself, and one to monitor that create stack workflow to check for timeouts and failures.  The monitor workflow is responsible for Rollback, for example.

The delete stack workflow is kicked off when delete stack is called.

The stack id is associated with the stack that is in question, and the other columns are the SWF fields associated with the workflows (runId, workflowId, and domain).
